            Slug = "assets-reference",
            Summary = "Edge-case and power-user reference for Assets: depreciation/cost bounds, GL sync, predictive maintenance, subcontracting, capability/role gating, photos, and deep-links.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Reference,
            EstimatedMinutes = 4,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 90,
            AppRoutes = """["/assets"]""",
            Tags = """["assets","reference","advanced"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Depreciation Options & Cost Bounds\n\nThe Acquisition section stores two fixed-asset accounting hints on every asset.\n\n- **Depreciation Method** maps to the `DepreciationMethod` enum: `Straight Line`, `Declining Balance`, and `Units of Production` (plus the blank/none option in the UI). The app only records the chosen method — it does **not** compute a depreciation schedule. Posting and the actual schedule are delegated to the external accounting provider.\n- **Acquisition Cost** is validated server-side in `CreateAssetCommandValidator`: when supplied it must be `InclusiveBetween(0, 1,000,000,000)` (bounded like a customer credit limit — above 1B is treated as a typo). Out-of-range values fail FluentValidation and the save returns 400. Cost is optional; omit it and the field is simply null.\n- `GlAccount` is capped at 100 chars; `Name` at 200; `SerialNumber` and `Location` at 100 and 200 respectively.\n\n## GL Auto-Population via Accounting Sync\n\n`GlAccount` is the boundary field between Forge and your books.\n\n- **Integrated mode** — when an accounting provider (`IAccountingService.IsConfigured == true`, e.g. QuickBooks Online) is connected, the GL account is sourced from the accounting sync rather than typed by the operator.\n- **Standalone mode** — with no provider connected, you enter the GL account by hand. This mirrors the wider Accounting Boundary: depreciation schedules, the general ledger, and bank reconciliation are never-in-app features regardless of mode, so Forge holds only the *reference* (account string + method), not the postings.\n\n## Predictive Maintenance Dashboard\n\nAsset condition and failure forecasting live in the separate **Maintenance** area, not on `/assets`. The Assets module is the equipment register (identity, status, hours, tooling, acquisition); the Maintenance feature reads those assets and layers predictive analytics (risk scores, remaining-useful-life, model registry) on top. Operating hours kept current on the asset (`PATCH /assets/{id}/hours`) are an input to usage-based intervals and predictive signals. Schedule-based PM on an asset is the manual, rule-based counterpart to the predictive forecasts.\n\n## Subcontract Send-Out / Receive-Back\n\nOutsourcing a single operation (send a part out for plating, heat-treat, anodize, then receive it back) is a `SubcontractOrder` flow, gated by **CAP-P2P-SUBCONTRACT** (distinct from the Assets capability). It is keyed off jobs/operations, not the asset record:\n\n- **Send-Out** — `POST /api/v1/jobs/{jobId}/operations/{opId}/send-out` creates a SubcontractOrder for an operation flagged `IsSubcontract`.\n- **Receive-Back** — `POST /api/v1/subcontract-orders/{id}/receive` closes the loop when the vendor returns the work.\n- **List** — `GET /api/v1/jobs/{jobId}/subcontract-orders`.\n- Status flows `Pending -> Sent -> InProcess -> Shipped -> Received -> QcPending -> Complete` (or `Rejected`). This is the \"Make + one outsourced step\" model — contrast with `ProcurementSource.Subcontract`, where the *entire* part is built by the vendor.\n\n## Capability & Role Gating\n\n- **CAP-MD-ASSETS** gates the whole `AssetsController`; with it disabled the gate middleware returns 403 + envelope and the route is hidden.\n- **Role** — the controller is `[Authorize(Roles = \"Admin,Manager,Engineer\")]`. Workers outside those roles cannot reach asset CRUD.\n- **CAP-MAINT-PM** gates the maintenance-schedule / log / create-job endpoints (preventive/predictive maintenance).\n- **CAP-MAINT-BREAKDOWN** gates the downtime (start/end/list) endpoints. A given install can have the asset register without breakdown tracking, or vice-versa — the capabilities are independent.\n\n## Asset Photo & Deep-Link\n\n- **Photo** — `Asset.PhotoFileId` (nullable) holds the file reference for an asset image/cover photo, stored via the file-attachment/storage layer rather than inline on the row.\n- **Deep-link** — the assets list auto-opens an asset's detail dialog when the URL carries `?detail=asset:{id}` (`autoOpenFromUrl()` reads it via the shared detail-dialog service). This is the canonical shareable link to a specific asset: send a teammate `/assets?detail=asset:42` and the record opens directly. The same `entityType:entityId` detail-dialog convention is used across other Forge list screens.","sections":[]}"""
        });

        Log.Information("Seeded Assets training modules");
